                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/15a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Collector
                            <persName type="to">Cobb</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-11T00:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1916, midnight.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Earnestly seek cooperation of Juarez and Chihuahua authorities to give every
                    facility to special train being sent by friends of deceased Americans who met
                    their deaths at hands of bandits yesterday to the end that the bodies may be,
                    recovered. If transfer of bodies to El Paso impracticable, use every effort to
                    have them given decent burial and have graves marked for identification and
                    removal later.</p>
                <p>Request authorities Chihuahua to send forces against bandits for capture and
                    punishment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
